1
00:00:04,705 --> 00:00:06,206
Look at all these rich people.

2
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:11,445
If everybody bought an ad from us,
we'd be drowning in money.

3
00:00:11,478 --> 00:00:13,547
You think like a pauper.

4
00:00:13,580 --> 00:00:15,515
You're no different.

5
00:00:15,816 --> 00:00:19,753
We don't sell ads to just anybody.
We choose our clients.

6
00:00:22,055 --> 00:00:23,624
Ms. Reiko!

7
00:00:25,259 --> 00:00:26,894
- Ms. Rio!
- Hello there.

8
00:00:27,661 --> 00:00:29,429
I'm playing today.

9
00:00:29,463 --> 00:00:31,398
- Really.
- Is Nami here too?

10
00:00:33,066 --> 00:00:36,036
Where has she gone?
You'll find her somewhere.

11
00:00:42,509 --> 00:00:46,246
Why am I avoiding Ms. Rio? Well...

12
00:00:46,780 --> 00:00:51,285
I'm actually getting somewhere
with the puppy-like boy.

13
00:00:51,318 --> 00:00:53,820
But his sister is my demonic boss.

14
00:00:54,788 --> 00:00:58,992
I decided to do my best so she'll
accept me as her brother's girlfriend.

15
00:00:59,026 --> 00:01:01,428
That's when I met Ms. Rio.

16
00:01:01,595 --> 00:01:04,197
She's pretty,
and even gave me love advice.

17
00:01:04,231 --> 00:01:06,333
She's an amazing person.

18
00:01:06,366 --> 00:01:11,505
But who would've imagined,
she was the one Junnosuke had loved.

19
00:01:11,538 --> 00:01:12,706
It's been ten years.

20
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:14,574
Why are you two together?

21
00:01:14,608 --> 00:01:17,477
I totally forgot, I had work to do.

22
00:01:18,378 --> 00:01:21,114
Well, I'll be going then.

23
00:01:21,815 --> 00:01:25,285
I was there when they had
their dramatic reunion.

24
00:01:25,319 --> 00:01:27,854
I will now introduce our guest.

25
00:01:28,255 --> 00:01:31,124
Ms. Rio Hasumi, the violinist.

26
00:01:32,225 --> 00:01:35,595
What happened between them afterwards?

27
00:01:36,229 --> 00:01:38,966
I want to know, I need to know, but...

28
00:01:38,999 --> 00:01:42,336
Thank you for inviting me today.

29
00:01:43,003 --> 00:01:44,471
I will now play for you.

30
00:01:57,617 --> 00:02:01,788
I wonder if Junnosuke
still loves Ms. Rio.

31
00:02:02,856 --> 00:02:05,192
And Ms. Rio too?

32
00:02:11,331 --> 00:02:15,435
I'm sorry, I lost sight of you
after I went to the ladies' room.

33
00:02:15,469 --> 00:02:17,771
Ms. Rio's violin was amazing.

34
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:18,772
Shintani.

35
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:21,408
Did you forget something?

36
00:02:24,611 --> 00:02:26,646
Reiko.

37
00:02:27,214 --> 00:02:28,615
Long time no see.

38
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:31,051
My daughter.

39
00:02:31,618 --> 00:02:33,420
That means...

40
00:02:33,687 --> 00:02:35,122
He's Junnosuke's dad!

41
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:39,092
Let me introduce you.
This is Shintani of Global Zest.

42
00:02:39,426 --> 00:02:41,962
He's the freshest
young entrepreneur today.

43
00:02:42,763 --> 00:02:45,432
I'm not sure of that,
but nice to meet you.

44
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:46,566
He's a smart guy.

45
00:02:47,067 --> 00:02:49,703
I'm Horai, Miyavi's editor-in-chief.

46
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:51,505
Miyavi?

47
00:02:51,538 --> 00:02:54,908
Um, my name is Nami Suzuki.

48
00:02:54,941 --> 00:02:57,177
An honor to meet you, sir.

49
00:02:58,111 --> 00:02:59,246
She's my assistant.

50
00:03:01,048 --> 00:03:03,316
Take good care of Reiko for me.

51
00:03:04,184 --> 00:03:06,453
I must be going now.

52
00:03:06,987 --> 00:03:08,555
- Excuse me.
- Later.

53
00:03:09,589 --> 00:03:10,857
Stay warm.

54
00:03:11,892 --> 00:03:14,995
I introduced myself to him, but...

55
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:18,598
Junnosuke hasn't even asked me
to go out with him.

56
00:03:18,932 --> 00:03:20,467
- You're home.
- I'm home.

57
00:03:24,037 --> 00:03:26,540
- Ju-Ju...
- You're home.

58
00:03:27,374 --> 00:03:29,242
- Goodbye.
- Hey wait!

59
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:32,612
Why are you running away?

60
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,382
And why are you here?

61
00:03:35,582 --> 00:03:37,951
You won't answer my calls or my texts.

62
00:03:39,086 --> 00:03:40,087
Are you avoiding me?

63
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:42,456
- No...
- Then why?

64
00:03:42,756 --> 00:03:44,658
Did I do something to make you mad?

65
00:03:46,493 --> 00:03:47,327
Well...

66
00:03:49,362 --> 00:03:52,699
Fine. I'm not leaving
till you tell me.

67
00:03:54,568 --> 00:03:56,570
No, you can't...

68
00:03:57,304 --> 00:03:58,605
The neighbors will see.

69
00:04:05,178 --> 00:04:07,581
Fine, you can come in.

70
00:04:10,717 --> 00:04:14,788
Oh My Boss! Love Not Included

71
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:16,656
Looks yummy.

72
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:23,163
You know, I want to eat dinner
and rest too.

73
00:04:23,697 --> 00:04:25,198
Yeah, I'm hungry too.

74
00:04:27,534 --> 00:04:30,637
- I'll make something.
- No, fine.

75
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:32,639
I'll make something.

76
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:34,407
Really?

77
00:04:34,841 --> 00:04:36,143
I'll take a bath then.

78
00:04:37,177 --> 00:04:38,145
A bath?

79
00:04:47,387 --> 00:04:49,422
I want to ask about Ms. Rio,
but I can't.

80
00:04:50,724 --> 00:04:53,493
Wait, is he going to stay the night?

81
00:04:55,228 --> 00:04:56,463
But...

82
00:04:57,164 --> 00:04:59,166
That means...

83
00:05:01,434 --> 00:05:03,170
J-Junnosuke.

84
00:05:08,742 --> 00:05:12,045
Junnosuke has become a black dog.

85
00:05:12,345 --> 00:05:13,647
Black Jun!

86
00:05:17,384 --> 00:05:21,054
Yeah. This is the real me.

87
00:05:21,655 --> 00:05:23,890
Pitch Black Jun.

88
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:25,592
Be prepared.

89
00:05:29,229 --> 00:05:30,096
No...

90
00:05:30,964 --> 00:05:34,134
No, don't Junnosuke!

91
00:05:38,205 --> 00:05:40,540
Should I not have worn this?

92
00:05:40,574 --> 00:05:43,043
No, go ahead.

93
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:46,346
That was yummy.

94
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,348
Thanks, Nami.

95
00:05:48,882 --> 00:05:50,684
- What?
- What what?

96
00:05:50,717 --> 00:05:53,653
I'm going to clean up.

97
00:05:54,721 --> 00:05:55,855
I'll get ready to sleep.

98
00:05:58,992 --> 00:06:00,293
Can I borrow these?

99
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:03,430
You're staying the night?

100
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:05,599
Yeah, can't I?

101
00:06:05,632 --> 00:06:09,536
Well, I mean...

102
00:06:09,569 --> 00:06:13,206
There's a lot more steps to take,
you know?

103
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,774
But it's not my first time.

104
00:06:14,808 --> 00:06:16,443
I know, you stayed here before.

105
00:06:16,476 --> 00:06:18,044
You stayed at my place too.

106
00:06:18,078 --> 00:06:20,614
Yes, I did. But...

107
00:06:28,021 --> 00:06:29,656
Already?

108
00:07:01,554 --> 00:07:02,389
OK

109
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:06,126
- Good work.
- Thank you.

110
00:07:07,494 --> 00:07:10,430
Ms. Horai OK'd it!

111
00:07:10,463 --> 00:07:12,866
The second issue of Miyavi is done!

112
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:15,669
All right!

113
00:07:15,702 --> 00:07:19,372
We're not done yet. How's everything
for the next issue going?

114
00:07:19,406 --> 00:07:20,607
Good work, Suzuki.

115
00:07:21,908 --> 00:07:23,643
I haven't slept well.

116
00:07:23,677 --> 00:07:26,780
Do you want to be my assistant
for my next feature?

117
00:07:26,813 --> 00:07:28,481
Huh? Really?

118
00:07:28,515 --> 00:07:30,950
Izumi's totally overworked.

119
00:07:31,217 --> 00:07:31,985
Oh dear.

120
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:35,855
- You scared me.
- It's OK'd.

121
00:07:36,222 --> 00:07:37,524
Want to give it a shot?

122
00:07:37,557 --> 00:07:39,492
But what will Ms. Horai say?

123
00:07:39,726 --> 00:07:40,527
I'm sorry to say,

124
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:46,399
but Monthly Gourmet
and Train Club Monthly

125
00:07:47,167 --> 00:07:50,136
will be officially discontinued.

126
00:07:51,004 --> 00:07:55,241
Times are tough,
but let's pull through somehow.

127
00:08:01,715 --> 00:08:03,049
Horai.

128
00:08:03,083 --> 00:08:04,651
It's Shintani from Global Zest.

129
00:08:04,951 --> 00:08:06,953
I have a proposal for you.

130
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:10,290
I'd like to buy some ads on Miyavi.

131
00:08:20,467 --> 00:08:22,068
These are tickets to the aquarium.

132
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:24,070
- For a date...
- A date?

133
00:08:26,473 --> 00:08:28,341
- Excuse me.
- Excuse me.

134
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:30,577
Ms. Horai, may I ask you something?

135
00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:34,280
Can I have Suzuki as
a temporary editing assistant?

136
00:08:34,647 --> 00:08:37,517
Suzuki's article in the house journal
was good.

137
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:39,386
I'll do my usual tasks, too.

138
00:08:48,928 --> 00:08:49,729
Why not?

139
00:08:52,098 --> 00:08:53,299
What did you just...

140
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:54,200
Give it a try.

141
00:08:56,002 --> 00:08:58,738
I'll let you off odd jobs for now.

142
00:08:59,506 --> 00:09:01,141
Seriously?

143
00:09:02,909 --> 00:09:04,978
Is something wrong?

144
00:09:05,011 --> 00:09:05,779
What?

145
00:09:05,812 --> 00:09:08,081
You're not your usual self.

146
00:09:09,616 --> 00:09:11,117
Hello everyone.

147
00:09:11,151 --> 00:09:12,752
Hello.

148
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:15,155
- Ms. Suzuki.
- Hi.

149
00:09:15,188 --> 00:09:19,692
About those aquarium tickets
you said you'd give me.

150
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:23,730
Actually, something came up.

151
00:09:23,763 --> 00:09:26,766
And Ms. Horai and I ended up
deciding to go.

152
00:09:27,267 --> 00:09:28,435
I'm sorry.

153
00:09:28,768 --> 00:09:30,170
You have a date!

154
00:09:31,504 --> 00:09:33,440
Well it's... Keep it down!

155
00:09:33,473 --> 00:09:34,774
I'm sorry.

156
00:09:34,974 --> 00:09:36,242
So that's why.

157
00:09:36,276 --> 00:09:38,011
Everything is clear now.

158
00:09:38,845 --> 00:09:42,015
Ms. Horai has been
acting strange today.

159
00:09:42,048 --> 00:09:43,817
It was because of love, huh.

160
00:09:44,284 --> 00:09:46,586
- I don't think...
- I know it is.

161
00:09:46,619 --> 00:09:48,755
Don't worry about the tickets.

162
00:09:48,788 --> 00:09:50,457
Enjoy your date.

163
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:51,524
Bye.

164
00:09:52,492 --> 00:09:54,260
Original Cinderella?

165
00:09:54,294 --> 00:09:57,530
We're starting an made-to-order
online shopping brand.

166
00:09:58,164 --> 00:10:01,501
I'd like to advertise it
solely in Miyavi.

167
00:10:02,335 --> 00:10:03,503
Solely?

168
00:10:03,536 --> 00:10:06,072
So beginning with your third issue,

169
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:10,510
I'd like to buy a special feature
and a yearly advertisement set.

170
00:10:10,543 --> 00:10:11,911
Thank you.

171
00:10:12,412 --> 00:10:16,449
But a lot of the ads are already sold
to other brands.

172
00:10:16,483 --> 00:10:18,818
I'm afraid it must wait
for the fourth issue.

173
00:10:18,852 --> 00:10:21,154
I understand, but still.

174
00:10:23,323 --> 00:10:25,358
You're telling me to move the others?

175
00:10:25,425 --> 00:10:29,295
We're prepared
to pay a good price for it.

176
00:10:29,329 --> 00:10:33,800
Considering Otowado's financial
situation, I think it's a good deal.

177
00:10:34,901 --> 00:10:37,370
- May I ask you something?
- Sure.

178
00:10:38,538 --> 00:10:43,076
Did the president of Horai Paperworks
ask you to do this?

179
00:10:43,109 --> 00:10:46,279
Yes, it's true that he suggested it.

180
00:10:46,746 --> 00:10:49,215
But I'm a man of business.

181
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:51,251
I decided based on my experience.

182
00:10:51,885 --> 00:10:52,719
I see.

183
00:10:53,019 --> 00:10:54,654
Give-and-take, don't you think?

184
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:03,663
The second issue.

185
00:11:04,531 --> 00:11:06,699
Here it is.

186
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,568
I love this magazine.

187
00:11:11,571 --> 00:11:12,805
Thank you.

188
00:11:16,576 --> 00:11:19,812
A few days later

189
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:30,723
Strawberry or chocolate banana?

190
00:11:31,057 --> 00:11:33,059
I'll have the chocolate banana.

191
00:11:33,092 --> 00:11:35,595
I knew it. I always have strawberry.

192
00:11:41,134 --> 00:11:42,702
You can't eat that.

193
00:11:42,735 --> 00:11:43,636
Sorry.

194
00:11:52,011 --> 00:11:54,847
It's the weekend,
so there's a lot of families huh.

195
00:11:54,881 --> 00:11:55,915
Yes, there is.

196
00:11:56,583 --> 00:11:57,750
Lots of families.

197
00:11:58,451 --> 00:11:59,886
Since it's the weekend.

198
00:12:01,821 --> 00:12:02,655
Um...

199
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:05,625
Well...

200
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:11,698
I'm sorry. I wanted to sell as many
copies of Issue Two as Issue One.

201
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:13,566
- In the next...
- Ms. Reiko.

202
00:12:14,367 --> 00:12:15,201
Yes?

203
00:12:15,234 --> 00:12:19,505
I want you to relax
and enjoy your day today.

204
00:12:21,441 --> 00:12:24,644
My ex-wife and I were in
the same industry too.

205
00:12:24,677 --> 00:12:26,846
All we talked about was our jobs.

206
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:28,748
I just couldn't relax.

207
00:12:29,616 --> 00:12:30,883
And things didn't work.

208
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:37,190
This is my first date in a long time.

209
00:12:37,857 --> 00:12:42,095
So I want to forget about my job
and enjoy the day.

210
00:12:45,131 --> 00:12:45,732
Got it.

211
00:12:48,701 --> 00:12:49,469
Sharks.

212
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:51,738
Did you know?

213
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:55,808
Sharks have a sixth sense.

214
00:12:57,744 --> 00:12:59,245
A literal sixth sense.

215
00:12:59,846 --> 00:13:04,550
All living things emit a very weak
electric current from their muscles.

216
00:13:05,318 --> 00:13:08,388
Sharks can sense that.

217
00:13:09,022 --> 00:13:13,493
So they can even find tiny creatures
hidden in the sand.

218
00:13:13,926 --> 00:13:15,061
You're very knowledgeable.

219
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:17,230
I looked it up yesterday.

220
00:13:18,197 --> 00:13:22,101
Guys do that. We study lots of trivia
before we go on dates.

221
00:13:23,736 --> 00:13:24,837
That's quite an effort.

222
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:30,810
I'm home.

223
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:38,951
Guess he's not here today.

224
00:13:45,058 --> 00:13:45,958
What's that?

225
00:13:49,929 --> 00:13:51,064
From Junnosuke Horai

226
00:13:51,164 --> 00:13:52,265
What?

227
00:14:06,079 --> 00:14:07,246
Clothes?

228
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:14,721
Hair wax?

229
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:20,126
Bowls and chopsticks?

230
00:14:24,163 --> 00:14:25,198
A pillow?

231
00:14:27,133 --> 00:14:28,334
A hotplate?

232
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:34,140
He's definitely planning a barbecue.

233
00:14:35,842 --> 00:14:37,510
Is he going to live here?

234
00:14:45,017 --> 00:14:48,154
I'll put them away next time I go.
Junnosuke.

235
00:14:48,254 --> 00:14:50,623
This is my house, you know.

236
00:14:53,860 --> 00:14:55,762
Why don't you just go home...

237
00:14:57,296 --> 00:14:59,565
- Ms. Rio?
- Should I not have come?

238
00:14:59,599 --> 00:15:02,135
No, I mean, why are you...?

239
00:15:02,168 --> 00:15:03,369
I asked at your work.

240
00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:06,405
You were at that party the other day,
weren't you?

241
00:15:06,472 --> 00:15:09,342
I wanted to hear what happened
with your lover.

242
00:15:10,209 --> 00:15:12,345
I bought some cake. Let's eat!

243
00:15:12,378 --> 00:15:14,881
- No, no wait!
- What?

244
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:17,617
My room is a mess right now.

245
00:15:18,985 --> 00:15:20,119
Is it...?

246
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:22,555
Him?

247
00:15:25,091 --> 00:15:28,027
Don't hide it from me. Hey!

248
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:29,662
- Come out!
- He's not...

249
00:15:30,096 --> 00:15:31,464
It's really going down now.

250
00:15:33,065 --> 00:15:34,200
Come out!

251
00:15:35,868 --> 00:15:36,969
Roachy!

252
00:15:37,937 --> 00:15:38,771
Where are you?

253
00:15:38,805 --> 00:15:39,605
Roachy?

254
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:42,408
She thinks it's a cockroach.

255
00:15:45,978 --> 00:15:48,281
Junnosuke's underwear!

256
00:15:48,314 --> 00:15:50,216
I must've tossed them from the boxes.

257
00:15:50,249 --> 00:15:51,551
Did you find him?

258
00:15:52,852 --> 00:15:54,754
I found you!

259
00:15:58,724 --> 00:16:00,593
- Got it?
- It got away.

260
00:16:02,261 --> 00:16:04,497
Hey, by the way.

261
00:16:05,031 --> 00:16:07,033
I see you have two toothbrushes.

262
00:16:10,436 --> 00:16:11,571
When did he...?

263
00:16:12,071 --> 00:16:14,240
Did Jun ask you out?

264
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:18,511
It's Jun, isn't it?

265
00:16:19,745 --> 00:16:20,713
You knew?

266
00:16:20,746 --> 00:16:23,583
You had it written all over your face
the other day.

267
00:16:24,517 --> 00:16:27,887
You and Jun, huh?
I'll be rooting for you.

268
00:16:30,122 --> 00:16:30,957
Um...

269
00:16:32,758 --> 00:16:35,194
Were you and Junnosuke...

270
00:16:35,228 --> 00:16:36,762
Yeah, we dated.

271
00:16:37,597 --> 00:16:38,798
It was years ago.

272
00:16:40,533 --> 00:16:43,636
Yeah, it bugs you doesn't it?

273
00:16:48,207 --> 00:16:52,178
Our families did business together.

274
00:16:52,211 --> 00:16:54,280
We played together since preschool.

275
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,417
I'm a year older than him.

276
00:16:59,185 --> 00:17:02,788
After high school,
I went to a music college in Italy.

277
00:17:03,556 --> 00:17:07,326
When I came back
for Christmas vacation,

278
00:17:07,793 --> 00:17:08,895
he asked me out.

279
00:17:09,262 --> 00:17:11,197
He asked you out?

280
00:17:11,430 --> 00:17:12,765
Yeah, I guess he did.

281
00:17:13,666 --> 00:17:15,968
Rio, will you go out with me?

282
00:17:18,170 --> 00:17:19,639
It'll be long distance.

283
00:17:19,672 --> 00:17:21,007
Distance doesn't matter.

284
00:17:24,343 --> 00:17:26,712
- Okay.
- Yay!

285
00:17:27,847 --> 00:17:31,117
So we did the long distance thing
for a while.

286
00:17:31,751 --> 00:17:34,520
Sorry, I can't go home this month.

287
00:17:35,922 --> 00:17:36,656
Why?

288
00:17:36,656 --> 00:17:38,824
I want to focus on the violin.

289
00:17:39,592 --> 00:17:41,928
This is my last chance.

290
00:17:42,528 --> 00:17:44,263
The violin is everything to me.

291
00:17:45,765 --> 00:17:47,800
I don't want it to end as a dream.

292
00:17:48,968 --> 00:17:50,770
I want to make it come true.

293
00:17:53,272 --> 00:17:54,140
A dream...

294
00:17:54,574 --> 00:17:56,943
And ten years passed. That's it.

295
00:18:01,981 --> 00:18:04,283
Sometimes, it's because of
those ten years

296
00:18:04,317 --> 00:18:07,920
that the feelings become stronger.

297
00:18:10,022 --> 00:18:13,392
I was in love with a childhood friend
for a long time too.

298
00:18:13,826 --> 00:18:19,298
Don't worry. Jun forgets everything
if he eats something sweet.

299
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:25,371
If Junnosuke still has feelings
for Ms. Rio...

300
00:18:26,072 --> 00:18:28,240
Come on, eat up.

301
00:18:29,208 --> 00:18:30,176
Thanks.

302
00:18:32,044 --> 00:18:35,448
I'd never have a chance.

303
00:18:37,883 --> 00:18:41,387
Should I decorate this shelf?

304
00:18:41,420 --> 00:18:43,322
Find something from that box.

305
00:18:43,522 --> 00:18:44,590
Good morning.

306
00:18:44,924 --> 00:18:47,126
Good morning.

307
00:18:47,159 --> 00:18:49,195
Jessica!

308
00:18:49,228 --> 00:18:52,365
- I had so much fun the other day.
- Me too!

309
00:18:52,398 --> 00:18:54,400
- Let's go to a hot spring again.
- Yeah.

310
00:18:54,433 --> 00:18:56,068
- Where should I change?
- Over here.

311
00:18:57,503 --> 00:18:59,238
Hello.

312
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:02,475
They're really close.

313
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:06,178
Ms. Wada uses her a lot.
I guess they're used to it.

314
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:10,649
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

315
00:19:10,683 --> 00:19:12,218
Hi Haruka.

316
00:19:12,451 --> 00:19:13,953
Good morning.

317
00:19:14,754 --> 00:19:15,721
Junnosuke?

318
00:19:15,755 --> 00:19:17,123
Good morning, Nami.

319
00:19:17,556 --> 00:19:19,058
I'm the photographer today.

320
00:19:19,859 --> 00:19:21,127
Hi, mean senpai.

321
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,562
Don't say that in front of him!

322
00:19:23,596 --> 00:19:24,363
Too late.

323
00:19:24,397 --> 00:19:26,999
Junnosuke!

324
00:19:27,033 --> 00:19:29,502
It's so nice to see you!

325
00:19:29,535 --> 00:19:30,636
I'll get set up.

326
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:33,506
Yes, thank you.

327
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:39,512
I got his number at the mixer.

328
00:19:40,179 --> 00:19:42,548
He's my type.

329
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:47,086
Editors have the right to choose,
right?

330
00:19:47,119 --> 00:19:48,988
You hurry up and become one too.

331
00:19:51,090 --> 00:19:54,527
Nami, you left the bathroom light on
the other day.

332
00:19:55,361 --> 00:19:56,495
Bathroom light?

333
00:19:56,529 --> 00:19:59,999
Why are you saying that now?
Couldn't that wait?

334
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:01,600
I just now remembered.

335
00:20:01,634 --> 00:20:03,836
Aw shucks, Mr. Jun.

336
00:20:05,938 --> 00:20:07,406
What's he talking about?

337
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:11,110
No, it's um...

338
00:20:13,179 --> 00:20:14,613
She's my girlfriend.

339
00:20:15,281 --> 00:20:16,782
What? Who?

340
00:20:17,483 --> 00:20:18,250
Nami.

341
00:20:18,818 --> 00:20:21,821
Suzuki is your girlfriend?

342
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:24,457
We're dating.

343
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:31,931
All right! You said it!

344
00:20:31,964 --> 00:20:35,201
He just called me his girlfriend.

345
00:20:35,968 --> 00:20:40,072
I need to hear that in slow motion.

346
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:42,775
She's my girlfriend.

347
00:20:43,609 --> 00:20:44,009
Slow motion

348
00:20:44,009 --> 00:20:51,650
She's my girlfriend.

349
00:20:52,818 --> 00:20:54,353
We're dating.

350
00:20:54,386 --> 00:20:54,653
Slow motion

351
00:20:54,653 --> 00:21:00,826
We're dating...

352
00:21:02,061 --> 00:21:06,098
He said it in front of everybody.

353
00:21:07,133 --> 00:21:09,135
You're totally the man!

354
00:21:09,635 --> 00:21:11,904
- Let's get set up.
- Sure.

355
00:21:12,638 --> 00:21:14,707
My heart is fluttering now too.

356
00:21:15,808 --> 00:21:18,377
I even feel younger.

357
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:19,411
Can I make room for my stuff?

358
00:21:19,445 --> 00:21:21,180
You're trying to get even comfier.

359
00:21:21,213 --> 00:21:22,515
A waste, huh?

360
00:21:22,548 --> 00:21:25,417
I wonder what it's like
to have your dream job.

361
00:21:25,451 --> 00:21:27,953
What use is there
in finding a reason to work?

362
00:21:27,987 --> 00:21:29,522
Ms. Horai sure gave us
a scare yesterday.

363
00:21:29,555 --> 00:21:30,956
You should rely on people more.

364
00:21:30,990 --> 00:21:32,958
What does it mean to protect Miyavi?

365
00:21:43,269 --> 00:21:44,236
I'm home.

366
00:21:45,104 --> 00:21:47,139
You're home. I'm home.

367
00:21:47,373 --> 00:21:48,407
You're home.

368
00:21:50,109 --> 00:21:50,876
Huh?

369
00:21:51,477 --> 00:21:54,113
Why are you staying here
all the time now?

370
00:21:54,146 --> 00:21:55,514
Because it's comfy here.

371
00:21:56,749 --> 00:21:57,650
Should I leave?

372
00:21:59,451 --> 00:22:01,187
My room isn't that big.

373
00:22:01,420 --> 00:22:03,556
But you can keep some stuff here.

374
00:22:04,156 --> 00:22:05,591
I'll keep it organized.

375
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:12,464
Can I make room for my stuff here?

376
00:22:12,965 --> 00:22:14,967
You're trying to get even comfier.

377
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,603
Come on, it'll work. Help me out.

378
00:22:25,911 --> 00:22:26,779
You know what?

379
00:22:28,147 --> 00:22:32,084
I was glad you said
I was your girlfriend.

380
00:22:35,354 --> 00:22:37,656
I wasn't really sure what we were.

381
00:22:39,124 --> 00:22:43,963
I didn't feel like I should ask you
about Ms. Rio either.

382
00:22:45,164 --> 00:22:46,031
And...

383
00:22:47,099 --> 00:22:51,570
If I asked
and you said you still liked her...

384
00:22:53,606 --> 00:22:55,407
I was too scared to ask.

385
00:22:59,411 --> 00:23:00,646
What?

386
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:03,883
You're so cute.

387
00:23:10,956 --> 00:23:13,092
Hey, stop it.

388
00:23:19,632 --> 00:23:20,499
Nami.

389
00:23:24,336 --> 00:23:25,838
Let's stay together forever.

390
00:23:34,613 --> 00:23:35,381
Yes.

391
00:23:38,417 --> 00:23:42,154
But if you bring
any more of your stuff here,

392
00:23:43,622 --> 00:23:46,292
- I'm throwing it out.
- Come on.

393
00:23:47,159 --> 00:23:48,761
Sorry!

394
00:23:50,362 --> 00:23:52,531
Be quiet! It's late!

395
00:23:54,867 --> 00:23:56,302
Sorry.

396
00:23:59,338 --> 00:24:00,239
Hey.

397
00:24:00,272 --> 00:24:01,407
Sorry.

398
00:24:06,712 --> 00:24:08,547
Photography contest results

399
00:24:08,580 --> 00:24:11,550
...was not chosen...

400
00:24:14,653 --> 00:24:18,257
Thank you for taking the time
for this lunch.

401
00:24:18,290 --> 00:24:19,925
Come on, stop that.

402
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:24,496
But we haven't sat down like this
in years.

403
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:29,635
Have some.

404
00:24:30,869 --> 00:24:31,670
Thanks.

405
00:24:32,538 --> 00:24:33,639
Where were you?

406
00:24:33,672 --> 00:24:34,540
Nothing.

407
00:24:37,509 --> 00:24:38,644
About the ad.

408
00:24:39,311 --> 00:24:41,513
You talked to Mr. Shintani,
didn't you?

409
00:24:42,414 --> 00:24:44,316
That's about all I could do.

410
00:24:45,084 --> 00:24:48,120
You can ask me for help
anytime too, Junnosuke.

411
00:24:48,854 --> 00:24:50,189
Yeah, thanks.

412
00:24:50,222 --> 00:24:53,859
This will be your last year
doing whatever you want.

413
00:24:54,259 --> 00:24:55,994
You've done enough, haven't you?

414
00:24:56,028 --> 00:24:58,130
I haven't really
accomplished anything.

415
00:24:58,163 --> 00:24:59,698
Aww, come on.

416
00:25:00,499 --> 00:25:03,936
So why did you go to Otowado, Reiko?

417
00:25:04,670 --> 00:25:07,873
Someone who helped me out in the past
asked me to join.

418
00:25:08,040 --> 00:25:11,043
You were editor-in-chief
of some magazine in Paris, right?

419
00:25:11,410 --> 00:25:13,178
What a waste of a good career.

420
00:25:14,646 --> 00:25:15,681
Drink up, Junnosuke.

421
00:25:15,714 --> 00:25:17,249
Thanks.

422
00:25:25,157 --> 00:25:26,925
A waste, huh.

423
00:25:27,726 --> 00:25:28,527
Anything the matter?

424
00:25:32,097 --> 00:25:33,265
Another please.

425
00:25:34,733 --> 00:25:35,934
Paris?

426
00:25:36,335 --> 00:25:37,936
For your graduation trip?

427
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:39,238
No, by myself.

428
00:25:39,238 --> 00:25:40,272
12 years ago

429
00:25:40,272 --> 00:25:44,410
There's a fashion school in Paris
called Esse Mode.

430
00:25:44,443 --> 00:25:46,445
I want to go visit it.

431
00:25:46,612 --> 00:25:48,580
But what for?

432
00:25:49,581 --> 00:25:53,152
I've actually been really into fashion
for a long time now.

433
00:25:53,685 --> 00:25:57,589
Of course, I'll prioritize
joining Horai Paperworks.

434
00:25:58,157 --> 00:26:02,928
But I just thought maybe
a career in fashion might work too.

435
00:26:05,831 --> 00:26:08,534
What are you talking about?
What a waste!

436
00:26:09,501 --> 00:26:10,736
A waste?

437
00:26:10,769 --> 00:26:13,872
You're graduating a top university
with flying grades.

438
00:26:13,906 --> 00:26:16,942
And you're the daughter
of the Horai family.

439
00:26:16,975 --> 00:26:18,477
What a waste!

440
00:26:22,614 --> 00:26:23,449
Your gimlet.

441
00:26:25,517 --> 00:26:28,287
I'm sorry, I remembered
I had some work to do.

442
00:26:29,121 --> 00:26:30,589
My, what a waste.

443
00:26:57,382 --> 00:26:58,250
Ms. Reiko?

444
00:26:59,318 --> 00:27:00,886
Mr. Ugajin...

445
00:27:04,723 --> 00:27:07,259
Minami Aoyama General Hospital

446
00:27:07,259 --> 00:27:08,694
You've been working too much.

447
00:27:09,127 --> 00:27:10,662
It's just anemia.

448
00:27:10,696 --> 00:27:11,864
Nah.

449
00:27:12,197 --> 00:27:15,367
You should rest up
for a couple of days.

450
00:27:16,401 --> 00:27:21,607
I'll have the advertising department
take over the talks with Global Zest.

451
00:27:21,974 --> 00:27:22,841
No.

452
00:27:23,175 --> 00:27:27,446
I must follow through with it for
Otowado and Miyavi to pull through.

453
00:27:28,146 --> 00:27:29,047
Actually...

454
00:27:29,548 --> 00:27:34,353
Mr. Shintani offered to buy ads
from our other magazines too.

455
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:36,321
He came to me.

456
00:27:37,456 --> 00:27:39,491
It's all thanks to you.

457
00:27:39,892 --> 00:27:43,829
If all goes well, we may be able
to avoid the merger.

458
00:27:48,634 --> 00:27:49,902
I'm so relieved.

459
00:27:52,437 --> 00:27:55,741
Suzuki, Ms. Horai sure gave us
a scare yesterday huh.

460
00:27:55,774 --> 00:27:56,909
What do you mean?

461
00:27:56,942 --> 00:27:58,577
You haven't heard?

462
00:27:58,610 --> 00:27:59,978
She was taken to the hospital.

463
00:28:01,613 --> 00:28:03,482
It wasn't anything serious.

464
00:28:03,515 --> 00:28:04,716
Really?

465
00:28:05,417 --> 00:28:06,652
She didn't tell me.

466
00:28:06,685 --> 00:28:10,255
Maybe she didn't want to bother you,
being an assistant now.

467
00:28:15,994 --> 00:28:17,029
Suzuki.

468
00:28:17,563 --> 00:28:18,830
Get moving.

469
00:28:19,431 --> 00:28:20,432
Sorry.

470
00:28:28,907 --> 00:28:30,208
Suzuki.

471
00:28:30,709 --> 00:28:33,045
I'm going to Gaienmae. You're coming.

472
00:28:38,417 --> 00:28:39,851
Done paying.

473
00:28:40,118 --> 00:28:41,053
Thanks.

474
00:28:44,056 --> 00:28:47,292
You're working too hard
on your own, Sis.

475
00:28:48,293 --> 00:28:49,428
Rely on people more.

476
00:28:50,996 --> 00:28:52,064
It gets lonely.

477
00:28:52,431 --> 00:28:54,633
How you won't depend on others.

478
00:28:57,202 --> 00:28:58,403
I have to get to work.

479
00:29:15,887 --> 00:29:16,855
Rio?

480
00:29:18,724 --> 00:29:21,326
Jun! What are you doing here?

481
00:29:22,194 --> 00:29:23,462
Sis got hospitalized.

482
00:29:25,263 --> 00:29:27,199
She's out now, and off to work.

483
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:30,068
What about you?

484
00:29:32,304 --> 00:29:33,939
Neurosurgery?

485
00:29:33,972 --> 00:29:36,375
Oh, it's nothing really.

486
00:29:36,742 --> 00:29:39,811
Just practiced a bit too much.
All violinists get it.

487
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:42,848
Later.

488
00:29:46,251 --> 00:29:47,119
Hey.

489
00:29:52,924 --> 00:29:54,159
I'm hungry.

490
00:29:58,263 --> 00:29:59,731
You never change, do you?

491
00:30:02,868 --> 00:30:04,269
Stand in over there.

492
00:30:15,514 --> 00:30:16,848
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

493
00:30:16,882 --> 00:30:19,751
We'd like to have the shoot
in that seat.

494
00:30:19,785 --> 00:30:22,054
What time can we start setting up?

495
00:30:22,087 --> 00:30:23,388
Anytime after ten.

496
00:30:23,922 --> 00:30:26,491
Okay, we'll start unloading then.

497
00:30:26,525 --> 00:30:28,994
They must be studying
to work in fashion.

498
00:30:31,997 --> 00:30:36,201
If I make my name here, I could become
editor-in-chief of a culture magazine.

499
00:30:36,234 --> 00:30:38,303
Is that your dream?

500
00:30:38,336 --> 00:30:41,773
Everyone that works here
feels pretty much the same way.

501
00:30:42,641 --> 00:30:44,042
Except for you.

502
00:30:46,378 --> 00:30:47,279
Stand over there.

503
00:30:53,285 --> 00:30:57,723
Have you always wanted
to become an editor?

504
00:30:58,924 --> 00:30:59,991
What now?

505
00:31:02,594 --> 00:31:05,597
I wonder what it's like
to have your dream job.

506
00:31:06,298 --> 00:31:07,299
Huh?

507
00:31:07,332 --> 00:31:09,201
I don't want to be presumptuous.

508
00:31:09,935 --> 00:31:13,305
But I think maybe if I were still
working under Ms. Horai,

509
00:31:13,338 --> 00:31:16,708
she might not have fallen ill.

510
00:31:18,744 --> 00:31:23,582
I always thought that a job
was something you did for someone.

511
00:31:24,149 --> 00:31:28,587
But you guys do what you want to do
for your jobs.

512
00:31:29,855 --> 00:31:31,957
That doesn't feel like a job for me.

513
00:31:32,524 --> 00:31:36,495
But more like getting paid
for what you do for a hobby.

514
00:31:36,528 --> 00:31:39,364
What use is there
in finding a reason to work?

515
00:31:40,999 --> 00:31:42,601
I know, but...

516
00:31:46,004 --> 00:31:47,005
Okay, done.

517
00:31:58,850 --> 00:32:01,720
Everybody thinks differently.

518
00:32:03,388 --> 00:32:04,689
So there's no answer.

519
00:32:07,192 --> 00:32:11,196
There's a lot of ways to think,
a lot of styles of working.

520
00:32:13,098 --> 00:32:18,103
And all that is what working is about.
Isn't that enough?

521
00:32:29,247 --> 00:32:31,516
Hey, what the heck?

522
00:32:32,651 --> 00:32:35,086
Those were wise words,
so I had to balance it out.

523
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:36,755
You little jerk.

524
00:32:38,423 --> 00:32:39,524
But...

525
00:32:40,859 --> 00:32:42,227
Thank you.

526
00:32:47,833 --> 00:32:48,633
Hey.

527
00:32:49,935 --> 00:32:52,337
If you're worried about Ms. Horai,

528
00:32:53,205 --> 00:32:56,441
don't wait for her to call for you
and just go.

529
00:32:59,411 --> 00:33:00,378
You're right.

530
00:33:07,686 --> 00:33:10,021
Based on data from the customers,

531
00:33:10,055 --> 00:33:12,490
we'll use AI
to design original dresses.

532
00:33:12,524 --> 00:33:14,960
It'll all be done online.

533
00:33:15,627 --> 00:33:17,362
That's incredible.

534
00:33:17,395 --> 00:33:19,598
Excuse me, another guest has arrived.

535
00:33:20,432 --> 00:33:21,933
Huh? Suzuki?

536
00:33:22,133 --> 00:33:23,702
I'm sorry.

537
00:33:23,835 --> 00:33:26,805
I was done working
so I was going to wait outside...

538
00:33:27,839 --> 00:33:29,007
But they told me to come in.

539
00:33:29,841 --> 00:33:32,177
Please, I don't mind.

540
00:33:33,511 --> 00:33:35,914
- Thank you.
- Stay quiet now.

541
00:33:35,947 --> 00:33:36,982
Yes, I'm sorry.

542
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:38,583
Hurry up.

543
00:33:39,551 --> 00:33:41,786
So, where were we?

544
00:33:42,153 --> 00:33:44,122
How everything will be online.

545
00:33:44,155 --> 00:33:47,993
Yes, I'd like Miyavi to do an article
on our made-to-order dresses.

546
00:33:48,026 --> 00:33:49,961
If possible, in your next issue.

547
00:33:49,995 --> 00:33:52,564
Of course.
We will clear some pages for it.

548
00:33:52,964 --> 00:33:53,865
Great.

549
00:33:54,966 --> 00:33:58,436
And about the made-to-order system.

550
00:33:58,803 --> 00:34:01,106
It's still under development.

551
00:34:03,108 --> 00:34:04,409
But the article?

552
00:34:04,643 --> 00:34:08,713
We'll have an existing dress ready,
so you can write it based on that.

553
00:34:09,047 --> 00:34:11,750
I see, yes that is possible.

554
00:34:12,017 --> 00:34:12,951
Ms. Horai.

555
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:19,157
But that wouldn't be
a made-to-order dress.

556
00:34:20,158 --> 00:34:22,127
- That's what people want to know.
- Suzuki.

557
00:34:22,594 --> 00:34:26,298
Ms. Suzuki,
we're talking business here.

558
00:34:26,331 --> 00:34:29,034
We will pay accordingly
for that advertisement.

559
00:34:29,067 --> 00:34:32,704
And Miyavi will write
an effective article for us.

560
00:34:32,737 --> 00:34:35,407
You're very right. Be quiet Suzuki.

561
00:34:35,941 --> 00:34:36,942
Yes, sir.

562
00:34:36,975 --> 00:34:38,610
Oh, and one more thing.

563
00:34:39,377 --> 00:34:42,113
You use that model Jessica
a lot, right?

564
00:34:42,147 --> 00:34:43,281
I'll need you to stop.

565
00:34:43,315 --> 00:34:44,482
- Jessica?
- Suzuki.

566
00:34:44,516 --> 00:34:47,319
I'm sorry. I was just with her
the other day.

567
00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:51,456
She's a model for one of our rivals.
We can't have that.

568
00:34:51,489 --> 00:34:52,590
I see.

569
00:34:52,991 --> 00:34:55,093
But if we did that...

570
00:34:55,827 --> 00:34:59,364
Miyavi would become like a pamphlet
for just one brand.

571
00:35:00,765 --> 00:35:02,067
Oh dear.

572
00:35:02,934 --> 00:35:06,171
Your father Mr. Horai suggested
that I make this offer.

573
00:35:06,938 --> 00:35:10,308
And I just wanted to help.

574
00:35:11,209 --> 00:35:12,344
- But...
- Be quiet.

575
00:35:15,647 --> 00:35:17,315
That's about all I could do.

576
00:35:17,349 --> 00:35:21,019
If all goes well, we may be able
to avoid the merger.

577
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:23,588
We...

578
00:35:26,057 --> 00:35:28,159
I must protect Miyavi.

579
00:35:31,329 --> 00:35:32,263
Ms. Horai.

580
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:35,567
How about we talk elsewhere
in private?

581
00:35:36,568 --> 00:35:38,536
Somewhere quieter would be nice.

582
00:35:40,638 --> 00:35:43,475
- Yes.
- We're sorry. I'll get a cab.

583
00:35:48,980 --> 00:35:49,814
Ms. Horai.

584
00:35:52,517 --> 00:35:54,719
What does it mean to protect Miyavi?

585
00:35:55,553 --> 00:35:59,724
If we can't make Miyavi the way
we feel is right, what use is there?

586
00:36:01,659 --> 00:36:05,797
I don't understand much yet
about magazine editing.

587
00:36:06,931 --> 00:36:11,703
But reading Miyavi
gives me so much strength.

588
00:36:12,103 --> 00:36:13,071
And...

589
00:36:13,972 --> 00:36:19,444
For the people reading Miyavi,
waiting for Miyavi to come out,

590
00:36:20,745 --> 00:36:23,448
I want Miyavi to stay the way it is.

591
00:36:57,482 --> 00:37:00,318
I might've really blown it this time.

592
00:37:19,204 --> 00:37:20,905
You were still here?

593
00:37:22,006 --> 00:37:24,375
I thought you left with Mr. Shintani.

594
00:37:25,510 --> 00:37:26,411
I did.

595
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:29,748
And declined his offer.

596
00:37:31,483 --> 00:37:34,819
There's something
I have to say to you.

597
00:37:38,456 --> 00:37:39,290
Thank you.

598
00:37:42,994 --> 00:37:47,532
Who would've thought you'd teach me
what it was I had to protect.

599
00:37:53,004 --> 00:37:53,905
That is all.

600
00:38:03,448 --> 00:38:04,582
Ms. Horai...

601
00:38:11,089 --> 00:38:14,459
I heard some of your magazines
are being discontinued.

602
00:38:14,726 --> 00:38:16,694
Miyavi won't last long either, huh?

603
00:38:18,897 --> 00:38:21,699
About what I had requested.

604
00:38:22,133 --> 00:38:23,201
Don't worry.

605
00:38:23,902 --> 00:38:28,173
Your editors will be safe with me.

606
00:38:31,709 --> 00:38:35,480
Anything you ask me to do.

607
00:38:41,186 --> 00:38:42,921
Two millefeuilles please.

608
00:38:42,954 --> 00:38:44,255
Of course.

609
00:38:45,089 --> 00:38:47,192
I'm going to eat it with Junnosuke.

610
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:51,629
Thanks for the delicious dinner.

611
00:38:52,497 --> 00:38:55,867
Meat is better
than any kind of medicine.

612
00:38:56,134 --> 00:38:57,769
Whatever.

613
00:38:57,969 --> 00:38:59,037
That's my motto.

614
00:39:01,339 --> 00:39:04,142
That's my bike there.

615
00:39:09,314 --> 00:39:10,148
Later.

616
00:39:26,130 --> 00:39:27,832
Sorry.

617
00:39:32,036 --> 00:39:35,006
Is it that bad? Your hand.

618
00:39:42,580 --> 00:39:44,882
Yeah, you know what?

619
00:39:46,517 --> 00:39:49,220
I just couldn't hit the notes
like I used to, right?

620
00:39:49,988 --> 00:39:51,222
Turns out...

621
00:39:53,658 --> 00:39:56,160
That devil editor-in-chief.

622
00:39:56,194 --> 00:39:58,963
She told me thank you!

623
00:39:59,497 --> 00:40:02,066
I have to tell Junnosuke now!

624
00:40:03,201 --> 00:40:04,802
Maybe his bike is still here.

625
00:40:13,311 --> 00:40:15,013
It'll get better, right?

626
00:40:16,114 --> 00:40:17,782
I can still play for now, but...

627
00:41:24,254 --> 00:41:27,858
Here. Have some cake.

628
00:41:28,225 --> 00:41:29,893
Wow, thanks.

629
00:41:31,028 --> 00:41:32,462
You're the best.

630
00:41:34,898 --> 00:41:36,333
Thank you.

631
00:41:38,669 --> 00:41:40,570
Looks delicious.

632
00:41:47,377 --> 00:41:48,345
What's wrong?

633
00:41:49,546 --> 00:41:51,682
Did Ms. Horai get at you again?

634
00:42:06,797 --> 00:42:08,098
Then what is it?

635
00:42:15,172 --> 00:42:16,473
Junnosuke.

636
00:42:18,375 --> 00:42:21,411
He was meeting with his ex in secret.

637
00:42:23,313 --> 00:42:24,348
So that's why.

638
00:42:26,750 --> 00:42:31,254
She's so pretty
and has a great personality.

639
00:42:32,189 --> 00:42:34,624
I'm nothing compared to her.

640
00:42:36,326 --> 00:42:38,562
That bites, huh.

641
00:42:38,795 --> 00:42:40,530
It's the worst, I swear.

642
00:42:48,372 --> 00:42:49,306
I mean...

643
00:42:50,907 --> 00:42:53,477
Sure, he saved me a bunch of times.

644
00:42:54,077 --> 00:42:59,282
He comes every time I'm feeling down,
and cheers me up.

645
00:43:00,083 --> 00:43:04,321
He makes me feel like
I'm okay being me.

646
00:43:13,630 --> 00:43:16,767
He said it was okay
to not have a dream.

647
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:19,569
Not that I'm against dreaming.

648
00:43:19,603 --> 00:43:21,304
But you don't need one, do you?

649
00:43:22,839 --> 00:43:27,644
Those words made me feel
so, so relieved.

650
00:43:30,981 --> 00:43:31,948
So...

651
00:43:35,519 --> 00:43:36,787
I love him to bits.

652
00:43:45,328 --> 00:43:47,497
But it's probably not me.

653
00:43:49,599 --> 00:43:51,601
The person he really loves...

654
00:43:54,571 --> 00:43:56,306
It isn't me.

655
00:44:02,879 --> 00:44:03,914
Ms. Suzuki.

656
00:44:21,665 --> 00:44:23,733
Symptoms and type of Dystonia

657
00:44:23,767 --> 00:44:28,905
Musician's dystonia is when the hands
stiffen when playing an instrument.

658
00:44:29,439 --> 00:44:34,811
For example, violinists experience
symptoms where the arm won't work.

659
00:44:49,759 --> 00:44:50,694
Hey.

660
00:44:53,930 --> 00:44:55,398
Are you waiting for Suzuki?

661
00:44:56,032 --> 00:44:56,867
Why?

662
00:44:57,167 --> 00:45:00,704
I'm not one to say,
but you should care for her more.

663
00:45:03,707 --> 00:45:05,709
It's none of your business.

664
00:45:05,742 --> 00:45:06,810
It is.

665
00:45:09,379 --> 00:45:11,448
If you're going to be like that...

666
00:45:12,482 --> 00:45:13,650
I'm not holding back anymore.

667
00:45:25,362 --> 00:45:27,797
What's that supposed to mean?

668
00:46:36,533 --> 00:46:37,767
What is it ?

669
00:46:39,436 --> 00:46:43,673
Oh yeah, the first draft.
Wait, I'm almost finished with this.

670
00:46:47,777 --> 00:46:48,812
Suzuki.

671
00:46:54,451 --> 00:46:56,119
I'm in love with you.

672
00:47:01,958 --> 00:47:02,926
Look.

673
00:47:05,629 --> 00:47:07,330
I would never make you cry.

674
00:47:19,342 --> 00:47:19,643
I won't let you con my daughter!

675
00:47:19,643 --> 00:47:21,578
Next episode

676
00:47:21,578 --> 00:47:23,179
Wait, I'm sorry...

677
00:47:23,213 --> 00:47:24,848
I need you to do something.

678
00:47:24,881 --> 00:47:26,650
The devil's smile again.

679
00:47:26,683 --> 00:47:28,585
Your kindness hurts me.

680
00:47:28,618 --> 00:47:29,185
I don't get you.

681
00:47:29,185 --> 00:47:30,553
This drama is fictional

682
00:47:30,553 --> 00:47:32,188
Figure it out yourself.
